                            <comment id="12833305" author="hossman" created="Sat, 13 Feb 2010 03:33:38 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;I fully expect stats.jsp will be deprecated in the next release of Solr in favor of the handler in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1750&quot; title=&quot;SolrInfoMBeanHandler - replacement for stats.jsp and registry.jsp&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1750&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1750&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#8211; BUT &amp;#8211; I still can&apos;t beleive such an anoying and yet trivial to fix bug was arround for so long ... especially since the incorrect fix for the XML attribute escaping is only half the problem: escapeCharData as still needed for the XML ELement content escaping.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;David: thanks for your prodding on this ... i committed your patch plus some additional fixes (r909705)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
